// TEST: Nested Function Malformed Where (rejects)
// A malformed where-clause on a nested `function` (unterminated `comm(`) must
// surface a real parse error, not be silently swallowed and re-reported as a
// misleading error at the `where`/`=`. Regression guard for the
// parseNestedFunction / parseFunctionDecl where-clause error-propagation fix:
// the `Error _ -> None` arm used to hide the genuine `Expected ')'` failure.
let result = {
    function f(x: Int64) where comm(x -> Int64 = x * 2
    f(3)
}
// EXPECT: parse failure — unterminated `comm(` in the where-clause.
